The paper deals with the design of a communication system involving multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) channels, which is a topic typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The system involves a relay station, which is a common topic in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new precoding technique to precompensate interstream interference, which is a signal processing technique that falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also deals with power allocation, which is a topic in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the design of a communication system, which is a topic in the Computer Communications (cs.COM) sub-category.
